1
00:02:12,791 --> 00:02:14,666
[NARRATOR]
Last time on Dragon Ball Z,

2
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:16,125
Gohan got a gift.

3
00:02:16,208 --> 00:02:18,208
[GOHAN] ...press this
red button to make it work?

4
00:02:18,291 --> 00:02:19,708
[BULMA] That's it.

5
00:02:22,166 --> 00:02:23,541
[TRUNKS] Awesome!

6
00:02:23,625 --> 00:02:24,833
Does it fit?

7
00:02:24,916 --> 00:02:29,000
Yeah! Why...
it's a super fit!

8
00:02:29,083 --> 00:02:30,500
[NARRATOR]
And when a high-jacked bus

9
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:32,375
went over a cliff,
it was time for

10
00:02:32,458 --> 00:02:35,333
the new superhero
to spring into action!

11
00:02:35,416 --> 00:02:38,666
That's right!
This bus stops here.

12
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:39,708
[VIDEL] Huh?!

13
00:02:39,791 --> 00:02:41,833
[NARRATOR] Going up, anyone?

14
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:45,583
There's a new hero in town!

15
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:49,791
[GOHAN] I am...
guardian of the city!

16
00:02:49,875 --> 00:02:51,750
The one and only!

17
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:55,083
[NARRATOR] That's right, Gohan!
Tell them how it is!

18
00:02:55,166 --> 00:02:57,833
[GOHAN] The Great Saiyaman!

19
00:03:10,958 --> 00:03:14,375
[GOHAN] I'm the Great Saiyaman!
Defender of truth!

20
00:03:14,458 --> 00:03:15,958
Protector of the innocent!

21
00:03:16,041 --> 00:03:22,625
Upholder of justice!
Doer of... good. Aah...

22
00:03:22,708 --> 00:03:24,541
How come when Dad
said that kind of stuff

23
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:25,833
it just rolled
right off of his tongue

24
00:03:25,916 --> 00:03:27,500
and sounded so natural.

25
00:03:27,583 --> 00:03:30,208
[GOTEN] Gee, it sounded
okay to me, Gohan!

26
00:03:30,291 --> 00:03:34,291
Nah! Thanks! Lets try this.

27
00:03:34,375 --> 00:03:36,708
Here we go!
Protector of the innocent!

28
00:03:36,791 --> 00:03:39,500
Defender of truth!
The light in the darkness!

29
00:03:39,583 --> 00:03:41,708
I have come to crush
the oppressors of this world

30
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:43,208
once and for all!

31
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:46,125
All right, you! Unhand her!

32
00:03:46,208 --> 00:03:49,583
Stand back! This is a job for...

33
00:03:49,666 --> 00:03:52,416
The Great Saiyaman!

34
00:03:53,458 --> 00:03:55,791
Well, whatd'ya think?

35
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:57,333
[GOTEN]
Yeah, that was awesome!

36
00:03:57,416 --> 00:04:00,375
It sounded even better
than the superheroes on TV!

37
00:04:00,458 --> 00:04:02,458
Can I be a superhero, too?

38
00:04:02,541 --> 00:04:05,375
I think one superhero's
enough for now.

39
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:07,875
Mom, what'd you think?
Did you hear that?

40
00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:09,833
I think it could
still use a little work.

41
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:11,625
But not tonight.
You've got to get up

42
00:04:11,708 --> 00:04:14,166
bright and early tomorrow,
Great Saiyaman.

43
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:17,125
No problem, Mom. I'm fine.

44
00:04:19,541 --> 00:04:21,083
[CHICHI] Gohan!
What are you doing?!

45
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:22,791
I thought you were
awake already!

46
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:25,125
School starts in ten minutes!

47
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,875
[GOHAN] Oh, man! I'm gonna
have to really move!

48
00:04:34,708 --> 00:04:38,666
[school bell chimes]

49
00:04:48,791 --> 00:04:49,666
Aah...

50
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:52,375
[GIRL]
Hi! I recognize you now!

51
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:54,250
You're in one of
my classes, aren't you?!

52
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:56,875
[GOHAN] Yeah! That's right!
Uh, English, isn't it?!

53
00:04:56,958 --> 00:04:58,416
You know, it's about to start.

54
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:01,083
Aren't you worried
about being late?

55
00:05:01,166 --> 00:05:03,000
[GIRL] No, not really.

56
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:05,041
[GOHAN]
You know... I can explain!

57
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:07,166
[GIRL] You can, huh?

58
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:09,708
[GOHAN laughs nervously]

59
00:05:09,791 --> 00:05:11,583
[GOHAN] See you in class!

60
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:14,958
[GOHAN thinking] Ah, man!
Stupid! Stupid! Stupid!

61
00:05:15,041 --> 00:05:17,791
Man! I really can't believe
I just did that!

62
00:05:17,875 --> 00:05:19,916
I haven't even been
a superhero for a week

63
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,208
and I've already
blown my cover!

64
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:25,791
[GOHAN thinking] I'm so stupid!
Stupid! Stupid! Stupid! Stupid!

65
00:05:27,625 --> 00:05:30,333
[GIRL thinking]
Wow! What an amazing guy!

66
00:05:30,416 --> 00:05:32,916
And he's really cute, too!

67
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,125
[murmuring]

68
00:05:36,208 --> 00:05:38,125
Gohan! You're on time!

69
00:05:38,208 --> 00:05:40,541
Little miracles happen everyday!

70
00:05:40,625 --> 00:05:42,500
[GOHAN sighs]

71
00:05:42,583 --> 00:05:44,333
[door opens, closes]

72
00:05:44,416 --> 00:05:45,791
Huh?!

73
00:05:48,291 --> 00:05:49,875
[GIRL giggles]

74
00:05:52,291 --> 00:05:53,500
--[GIRL] Mmm!
--[PROFESSOR] All right class,

75
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:56,166
let's continue where
we left off yesterday.

76
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:58,791
Now what did
Thoreau mean when he said:

77
00:05:58,875 --> 00:06:02,708
"The mass of men lead lives
of quiet desperation." Videl?

78
00:06:02,791 --> 00:06:04,125
[VIDEL]
I think that he meant that

79
00:06:04,208 --> 00:06:06,458
most people are unhappy inside.

80
00:06:06,541 --> 00:06:08,375
[PROFESSOR] Very good.
And what did he

81
00:06:08,458 --> 00:06:10,708
attribute this to, Gohan?

82
00:06:10,791 --> 00:06:12,750
[ERASA] Huh?

83
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:16,000
Is anybody home?

84
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:18,791
So... hm, we have a slacker.

85
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:20,625
[GOHAN] Oh, my gosh!
I shouldn't have landed there.

86
00:06:20,708 --> 00:06:22,166
That was so stupid!

87
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:23,625
I'll bet the whole
school's going to know

88
00:06:23,708 --> 00:06:25,041
by the end of the day!

89
00:06:25,125 --> 00:06:26,333
[PROFESSOR] Gohan!

90
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:29,416
Huh? Aaah! Sir! What?!

91
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,166
[CLASSMATES chuckling]

92
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:33,416
So this is the way you
want it to be, huh, Gohan?!

93
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,583
I was expecting more from you!

94
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:38,333
Sir! Yes, sir!

95
00:06:38,416 --> 00:06:40,166
[VIDEL sneezes]

96
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:41,583
[PROFESSOR] Listen up, class!

97
00:06:41,666 --> 00:06:44,291
I don't give lashes or
make you wear a dunce-cap!

98
00:06:44,375 --> 00:06:46,958
But after you hold those water
buckets for fifteen minutes,

99
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:48,958
you're going to wish I did!

100
00:06:49,041 --> 00:06:51,625
Do you feel your shoulders
burning, Mister Gohan?!

101
00:06:51,708 --> 00:06:53,125
Oh. Yes, sir.

102
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:55,916
[PROFESSOR] Good! Now who
can tell us what Thoreau felt

103
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,166
was causing the
inner desperation that he

104
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:00,083
sensed in his peers?

105
00:07:00,166 --> 00:07:03,208
What do you think, Miss Angela?

106
00:07:03,291 --> 00:07:05,125
[ANGELA sighs]

107
00:07:05,208 --> 00:07:07,750
Miss Angela...

108
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,625
Hmm...

109
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:11,541
Let's start
with an easier question.

110
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:13,208
Angela, do you know
where you are?

111
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:14,875
Uh-huh.

112
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:17,875
All right, then! Spit it out!

113
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:21,958
Uh... I'm sorry, Professor!
I don't know!

114
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,000
I don't know anything!

115
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:26,416
[PROFESSOR] Uh, Angela,
perhaps you should, uh,

116
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,791
visit the counselor.

117
00:07:27,875 --> 00:07:30,625
[ANGELA] No! No!
I need to be punished!

118
00:07:30,708 --> 00:07:32,750
[PROFESSOR] Very well.
You can listen to the lecture

119
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,333
through the window
with Mister Gohan!

120
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:36,625
Okay, sir!

121
00:07:36,708 --> 00:07:37,958
[PROFESSOR] Huh....?

122
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:41,333
[CLASSMATES murmur]

123
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:43,333
[ANGELA] Thanks, Professor!

124
00:07:43,416 --> 00:07:45,333
My word!

125
00:07:45,416 --> 00:07:46,416
[ANGELA] Hi.

126
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,791
Hi! You, too?

127
00:07:47,875 --> 00:07:51,416
Yeah! Gosh!
I was naughty, too!

128
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:55,041
Yep! Mmm.

129
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:56,000
Ooh.

130
00:07:56,083 --> 00:07:57,250
[ANGELA giggles]

131
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:58,833
[chuckles nervously]

132
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:01,291
[GOHAN thinking]
Oh, man! This is just great!

133
00:08:01,375 --> 00:08:02,875
What am I going to do now?

134
00:08:02,958 --> 00:08:05,583
--[ANGELA] Gohan!
--[GOHAN] Huh?

135
00:08:05,666 --> 00:08:08,166
Uh... yeah? What?

136
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:10,833
Nothing! But do you have
a steady girlfriend?

137
00:08:10,916 --> 00:08:13,083
No. I don't.

138
00:08:13,166 --> 00:08:15,958
Wonderful!
How 'bout dating me then?!

139
00:08:16,041 --> 00:08:19,333
Well, gosh! I... uh...

140
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:22,041
You think I'm ugly!
Don't you?!

141
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:24,166
Just say it!
You don't like me!

142
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:25,916
You think I'm ugly!

143
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,708
No! No! That's not true!

144
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:30,708
[ANGELA] Then why won't you go
out with me if it's not true?!

145
00:08:30,791 --> 00:08:32,666
It's just...

146
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:33,958
If you don't go out with me,

147
00:08:34,041 --> 00:08:35,875
I'll tell everyone your secret!

148
00:08:35,958 --> 00:08:38,166
[GOHAN squeals] You wouldn't!

149
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:41,500
I sure would! Just try me!

150
00:08:41,583 --> 00:08:43,416
Uh... Please don't!

151
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,583
[ANGELA] I don't understand!
Why won't you go out with me?

152
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:49,791
I thought we could start dating
and keep the secret between us!

153
00:08:49,875 --> 00:08:51,250
But you don't like me!

154
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,750
That's not true!
Let's go out!

155
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,375
You really mean it?!

156
00:08:55,458 --> 00:08:58,541
Yeah! [GOHAN chuckles]

157
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:00,083
Uh! Oh...

158
00:09:00,166 --> 00:09:01,375
[ANGELA cheers, giggles]

159
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:04,583
Great! Great!
We are going to have a blast!

160
00:09:04,666 --> 00:09:06,458
You just wait! Cool!

161
00:09:06,541 --> 00:09:07,708
Eh...

162
00:09:07,791 --> 00:09:10,875
Awesome! I'll see you
tomorrow then, okay?!

163
00:09:10,958 --> 00:09:12,541
I'll meet you in front
of the train station

164
00:09:12,625 --> 00:09:14,500
at one o'clock!

165
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:20,666
How did I get myself
into this predicament?!

166
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,833
Superheroes aren't
supposed to get blackmailed!

167
00:09:22,916 --> 00:09:24,500
That just doesn't
happen that way.

168
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:26,000
What am I gonna do?

169
00:09:26,083 --> 00:09:28,125
Maybe I should have Bulma
make me a different costume

170
00:09:28,208 --> 00:09:30,125
and just call
myself something else!

171
00:09:30,208 --> 00:09:32,000
How could I do this to myself?

172
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:36,083
I mean, I've never even
been on a date! This is crazy!

173
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:44,500
[CHICHI humming]

174
00:09:44,583 --> 00:09:45,416
[door opens]

175
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:46,666
[GOHAN] Hey, Mom! I'm home!

176
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,625
[CHICHI] Hi, sweetheart!
How was your day?

177
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:49,958
[GOHAN] Pretty good!

178
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:52,000
Except that I have to
go out on a date tomorrow.

179
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:54,916
[CHICHI] You have to go?
That's a likely story.

180
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,458
You know that I'm sending you
to school to learn, Gohan.

181
00:09:57,541 --> 00:09:59,250
You're going to need
your free time to study.

182
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:02,166
[GOHAN] No, I'm serious!
I have to go! She's forcing me!

183
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:04,208
Oh. Yes, I see!

184
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:05,750
I guess things
haven't changed that much

185
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:07,375
since I was a kid after all.

186
00:10:07,458 --> 00:10:09,208
I remember the first time
I made your father

187
00:10:09,291 --> 00:10:11,125
go out on a date with me.

188
00:10:11,208 --> 00:10:13,708
[GOHAN] You made him?

189
00:10:13,791 --> 00:10:15,291
Did you blackmail him?

190
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:18,458
[CHICHI] Oh, no! I don't think
I was that smart at the time.

191
00:10:18,541 --> 00:10:20,500
I was just a little girl.

192
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:23,791
[YOUNG CHICHI giggles]

193
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:25,041
You know what? Gosh!

194
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:26,416
This feels like
we're just hanging out!

195
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,000
Is there anything special
we're supposed to do

196
00:10:28,083 --> 00:10:29,666
since we're on a date?

197
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:32,000
Well, silly!
That's up to you!

198
00:10:32,083 --> 00:10:33,750
You're the boy and
the boy is supposed to

199
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,791
think of the most
pleasurable thing to do

200
00:10:35,875 --> 00:10:39,291
and then try to coax the girl
into doing it with him.

201
00:10:39,375 --> 00:10:44,250
Oh, I think I get it now!
The most pleasurable thing!

202
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:46,916
Goku, you're so adorable!

203
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,791
[YOUNG CHICHI] Aaahhh!
[YOUNG GOKU yells]

204
00:10:49,875 --> 00:10:50,625
[YOUNG GOKU laughs]

205
00:10:50,708 --> 00:10:52,625
[YOUNG CHICHI yells]

206
00:10:54,916 --> 00:10:56,333
[YOUNG GOKU laughs]

207
00:10:57,583 --> 00:10:59,583
[YOUNG GOKU]
Wow! This dating is fun!

208
00:10:59,666 --> 00:11:03,416
[YOUNG CHICHI] Goku! This isn't
exactly what I had in mind!

209
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:10,458
[CHICHI sighs] You're father
was such a rowdy boy.

210
00:11:10,541 --> 00:11:12,291
We spent the entire
day fighting.

211
00:11:12,375 --> 00:11:15,250
What a great
first date that was!

212
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:17,625
Wow, gosh.

213
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:42,708
♪

214
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:45,541
Hm. Huh?

215
00:11:46,125 --> 00:11:49,125
Hey! What's up?!
Thanks for coming!

216
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:53,250
You're so sweet! So, what are
we going to do today?!

217
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:55,833
Well, I've never been
on a date before.

218
00:11:55,916 --> 00:11:58,250
Is there something
that you want to do?

219
00:11:58,333 --> 00:11:59,625
Mmmnuuuuh...

220
00:11:59,708 --> 00:12:03,083
Oh, well let's think about it.
Let's see here!

221
00:12:03,166 --> 00:12:07,416
Hey! What about a movie?!
I love movies!

222
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,708
[GOHAN] Yeah, sure.
A movie sounds fun!

223
00:12:09,791 --> 00:12:12,250
[ANGELA] Great!
It's settled then! Let's go!

224
00:12:15,541 --> 00:12:18,375
[ANGELA] Come on, silly!
We're going to miss the start!

225
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,416
[CHAD] Listen, Loretta!

226
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:29,375
There's nothing
that can come between us.

227
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:32,333
Like, you're a great wave
in the ocean, y'know.

228
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:34,333
Once I get on it,
I know I'm gonna ride it

229
00:12:34,416 --> 00:12:36,125
all the way in to shore, baby!

230
00:12:36,208 --> 00:12:38,166
[LORETTA] And then the wave
crashes on the beach

231
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:40,375
and you go hop
on a different one!

232
00:12:40,458 --> 00:12:41,625
Is that it?

233
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:44,416
[CHAD] What do you mean,
baby?! We're soulmates!

234
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:47,166
[LORETTA] I found your letter
to Katy, Chad!

235
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:49,125
You... ignoramus!

236
00:12:49,208 --> 00:12:52,000
[CHAD]
Hey, wait, Loretta! Don't go!

237
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:53,833
You don't even wanna
be here with me!

238
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:55,666
Well, forget you!

239
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,000
--[GOHAN] No! Angela!
--[CHAD] That's not true,

240
00:12:57,083 --> 00:12:57,958
--[GOHAN] That's not true! Uh!
--[CHAD] Loretta!

241
00:12:58,041 --> 00:12:59,708
Wait! Angela!

242
00:12:59,791 --> 00:13:00,958
Excuse me. Pardon me.

243
00:13:01,041 --> 00:13:03,375
Hey! I'm sorry! Hold on!

244
00:13:03,458 --> 00:13:07,375
Sorry! Pardon me. Excuse me.
Just comin' through here...

245
00:13:07,458 --> 00:13:09,958
Angela! Wait up!

246
00:13:10,041 --> 00:13:12,375
Hey! I'm sorry!

247
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:15,958
It's just that those
romance movies put me to sleep.

248
